---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Reactables - Home" showDesktopNav={false} hideHamburger showGetStartedBtn>
	<div class="home-page">
		<section class="hero">
			<div class="container">
				<img class="hero__logo mb-3" src="/white-transparent.png" />
				<h1>Reactables</h1>
				<p class="hero__description">Reactive state management with a flexible and extensible API</p>

				<a href="/getting-started/introduction">
					<button class="btn btn-lg btn-outline-primary">Get Started</button>
				</a>
			</div>
		</section>
		<section class="features">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="row">
					<div class="col-12 col-lg-4 features__item">
						<img class="features__icon" src="/rxjs-logo-black-white.png" />
						<h4>Reactive</h4>
						<p>Data flow is <strong>uni-directional</strong> through reactive streams making state changes <strong>highly predictable</strong>.</p>
						<p>Reactive is declarative - means more time to <strong>focus on what</strong> you want to achieve in your buisness logic and <strong>save time on how</strong> it is implemented.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="col-12 col-lg-4 features__item">
						<img class="features__icon" src="/flexible.png" />
						<h4>Flexible</h4>
						<p>Reactables can manage both persisting global <strong>application state</strong> and local <strong>ephemeral state</strong> such as forms.</p>
						<p>It is also framework agnostic and can work with any UI layer.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="col-12 col-lg-4 features__item">
						<img class="features__icon" src="/testing.png" />
						<h4>Testability</h4>
						<p>Reactables are <strong>decoupled from the UI layer</strong> so they can be developed and <strong>unit tested</strong> without the need to render any components.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

		</section>
</div>
</Layout>

<style lang="scss">
	.hero {
		color: #fff;
		text-align: center;
		padding-top: 6.5rem;
		padding-bottom: 6.5rem;
		background-color: #4188d1;

		&__logo {
			width: 100px;
		}

		&__description {
			font-size: 1.25rem;
		}
	}
	.features {
		h4 {
			text-align: center;
		}

		&__icon {
			width: 100px;
		}

		&__item {
			display: flex;
			flex-direction: column;
			align-items: center;
			padding-top: 2rem;

			@media screen and (min-width: 992px) {
				padding-top: 4rem;
				padding-bottom: 4rem;
			}

			img {
				margin-bottom: 1rem
			}
		}
	}
</style>
